2.sl_source: "Vem, da je to navadno mestece, toda ne predstavljam si, da bi živela drugje."
2.en_source: "I know it's just a little town, but I couldn't imagine living anywhere else."
2.sl_trans: "Vem, da je to le majhno mesto, vendar si ne morem predstavljati, da bi živel kje drugje."

3.sl_source: Tu sem odrasla in hodila v šolo.
3.en_source: I grew up here, I went to school here.
3.sl_trans: Tu sem odraščal in se šolal.

8.sl_source: Precej dolgo se mi že ni oglasil.
8.en_source: I haven't heard from him in quite a while.

11.sl_source: "Ne vem, ali bi Ruth priznala, ampak po mojem še ona ne ve, kje je."
11.en_source: "I don't think she'd admit it, but I don't even think Ruth knows where he is."
11.sl_trans: "Mislim, da tega ne bi priznala, ampak mislim, da Ruth sploh ne ve, kje je."

12.sl_source: "Zdi se, da ti gre v redu."
12.en_source: You seem to be doing okay.
12.sl_trans: Zdi se, da vam gre dobro.

16.sl_trans: Toda z nami je vse v redu.

22.en_source: "For one thing, I move around a lot."

23.en_source: "Colombia, Guatemala, the Philippines Mexico, New Zealand, New Guinea."
23.sl_trans: "Kolumbija, Gvatemala, Filipini Mehika, Nova Zelandija, Nova Gvineja."

24.en_source: Wherever there's a volcano with an attitude.
24.sl_trans: Povsod, kjer je vulkan z vedenjem.

25.en_source: It makes it hard to settle down.
25.sl_trans: Zaradi tega se je težko ustaliti.

35.sl_source: Pred štirimi leti je v Kolumbiji izbruhnil vulkan.
35.en_source: "Four years ago, a volcano erupted in Colombia."
35.sl_trans: "Pred štirimi leti je v Kolumbiji izbruhnil vulkan."

36.sl_source: "Z Marianne sva mislila, da imava dovolj časa za umik."
36.en_source: Marianne and I thought we had enough time to get out.
36.sl_trans: Z Marianne sva mislila, da imava dovolj časa, da se umakneva.

38.en_source: We got too close to the show.

40.sl_source: "Če ta gora izbruhne in če jo raznese kot goro Saint Helens, bo rušilni val tu v eni minuti."
40.en_source: If this thing blows and if she does a Mount Saint Helens the blast will get here within a minute.
40.sl_trans: Če se bo ta stvar raznesla in če bo naredila Mount Saint Helens, bo eksplozija prišla sem v minuti.

41.sl_source: "Upam, da se motiš glede našega vulkana."
41.en_source: I hope you're wrong about our volcano.
41.sl_trans: Upam, da se glede našega vulkana motite.

42.sl_source: "Če se ne, pa sem vesela, da si tu."
42.en_source: "But if not, I'm glad you're here."
42.sl_trans: "Če pa ne, sem vesel, da si tukaj."

48.en_source: They're in the back of the van.

51.en_source: "Everyone, this is Rachel Wando, the mayor of the town."
51.sl_trans: "Vsi, to je Rachel Wando, županja mesta."

52.en_source: I thought you could use some coffee.
52.sl_trans: Pomislil sem, da bi ti prav prišla kava.

53.sl_source: "Ker ne vem, kakšno pijete, sem prinesla kapučine, zate pa navadno."
53.en_source: "Not knowing what you like, I brought cappuccinos except for regular for you."
53.sl_trans: "Ker nisem vedel, kaj imaš rad, sem ti prinesel kapučino, razen navadnega."

57.en_source: I could really use a good fix.
57.sl_trans: Resnično bi lahko uporabil dober popravek.

58.en_source: What kind of coffee machine do you use?

62.en_source: You probably keep your beans in the freezer.

64.sl_source: Nikoli jih ne hranite v zamrzovalniku.
64.en_source: Never keep your beans in the freezer.
64.sl_trans: Fižola nikoli ne shranjujte v zamrzovalniku.

67.sl_source: Tole mesto se pa morda splača rešiti.
67.en_source: This town just might be worth saving.
67.sl_trans: To mesto je morda vredno rešiti.

71.en_source: Best looking mayor I've ever seen.
71.sl_trans: Najuglednejši župan, kar sem jih kdaj videl.

74.sl_source: "Takole, fantje, s temle smo v igri."

77.sl_source: "Če bo tale gora zaplesala, bomo vedeli za to."
77.en_source: "If this mountain's going to rock and roll, we're going to know about it."
77.sl_trans: "Če se bo ta gora razgibala, bomo o tem vedeli."

78.sl_source: "Kako je bilo sinoči na večerji, Harry?"
78.en_source: "So, how was dinner last night, Harry?"

79.sl_source: "Terry, daj mi mir in mi nehaj iskati ženske."
79.en_source: "Terry, why don't you just give it a break and stop trying to fix me up?"
79.sl_trans: "Terry, zakaj se ne odvadiš in me nehaš popravljati?"

80.en_source: I have great taste in women.

81.en_source: When did I ever steer you wrong?
81.sl_trans: Kdaj sem vas kdaj narobe usmeril?

85.sl_source: Po mojem sta imela veliko skupnega.
85.en_source: I thought you'd have a lot in common.
85.sl_trans: Mislil sem, da imata veliko skupnega.

86.en_source: She said she was into rocks.
86.sl_trans: Rekla je, da se ukvarja s kamni.

96.en_source: You getting the hang of this thing?
96.sl_trans: Se že spoprijemate s to stvarjo?

97.sl_source: "Včasih še malo škriplje, toda mislim, da dojemam zadevo."
97.en_source: "It's still kind of goosey but, yeah, I think I'm getting it."
97.sl_trans: "Še vedno je nekoliko gusarska, ampak ja, mislim, da jo dobivam."

116.en_source: We've been recording between 25 and 75 earthquakes per day.
116.sl_trans: Na dan zabeležimo od 25 do 75 potresov.

122.en_source: This little puppy's called Spider Legs.
122.sl_trans: Ta kuža se imenuje Spider Legs.

123.sl_source: "V akcijo gre, ko je za nas prenevarno."
123.en_source: She goes in when it's too dangerous for us.
123.sl_trans: Vstopi, ko je za nas preveč nevarno.

125.en_source: "Actually, we'll take gas readings up front."

126.sl_source: Potem bomo video posnetke poslali v bazo.
126.en_source: "Then, we'll send video back here to home base."
126.sl_trans: "Nato bomo poslali videoposnetek nazaj v domačo bazo."

129.en_source: Now try to keep the weight on that one.
129.sl_trans: Zdaj poskusite obdržati težo na tem.

131.en_source: Keep the weight on this one-

137.sl_source: "Če se bo kar naprej zatikalo, ga ne bom vzel gor."
137.en_source: "If this keeps screwing up, I don't want to take it up there."
137.sl_trans: "Če se bo to še naprej kvarilo, nočem, da bi se odpravil tja gor."

139.en_source: I'm going to fix this once and for all.
139.sl_trans: To bom enkrat za vselej odpravil.

142.sl_source: "Samo glej, da stvar pritrdiš nazaj, preden NASA izve."
142.en_source: Just be sure to put the thing back on before NASA finds out.
142.sl_trans: Samo poskrbite, da jo boste namestili nazaj, preden NASA to ugotovi.

146.sl_source: Poba je nedvomno pripravljen za izlet.
146.en_source: Big boy's definitely ready to see the sights.
146.sl_trans: Veliki fant je vsekakor pripravljen na ogled znamenitosti.

154.sl_source: Od vsakega pričakujem opravičilo in pivo.
154.en_source: I expect apologies and six-packs from each one of you.
154.sl_trans: Od vsakega od vas pričakujem opravičilo in šest piva.

155.sl_source: "Hočeš medaljo, ker si dosegel, da stvar dela?"
155.en_source: Are you looking for a medal because you got the thing to work?
155.sl_trans: Ali iščete medaljo, ker vam je stvar delovala?

159.en_source: It ought to be working better.

160.en_source: It lost 15 pounds of ugly fat.

163.sl_source: Tamle na robu kraterja imamo manjšo geotermično aktivnost.
163.en_source: We got some minor geothermal activity there on the edge of the crater.
163.sl_trans: Na robu kraterja smo opazili manjšo geotermalno aktivnost.

164.en_source: Pan to the right a little bit.

165.en_source: I want to have a look at the lava dome.
165.sl_trans: Želim si ogledati kupolo iz lave.

167.en_source: Terry's masterpiece is a piece of junk.

168.en_source: Show me the leg that isn't working.
168.sl_trans: Pokaži mi nogo, ki ne deluje.

170.en_source: "Yeah, we copy, you have a problem."

171.sl_source: Bom pač metal kamne v prekleto reč.
171.en_source: I'll just throw rocks at the goddamn thing.
171.sl_trans: V to prekleto stvar bom samo metal kamenje.

172.sl_source: Dol bom šel in ga lastnoročno obdelal.
172.en_source: I think I'll go down there and give it the personal touch.
172.sl_trans: Mislim, da se bom odpravil tja in jo osebno uredil.

185.sl_source: Tole se mi ne zdi pametno.
185.en_source: I don't think this is a smart idea.
185.sl_trans: Mislim, da to ni pametna zamisel.

188.en_source: "Listen Terry, why don't we just forget Spider Legs for now and get your backside back up here, okay?"
188.sl_trans: "Poslušaj, Terry, zakaj ne bi za zdaj pozabili na pajkove noge in se vrnili sem, dobro?"

189.sl_source: "Terry, kaj ko bi za zdaj pustila Pajka in tvojo zadnjico spravila nazaj gor?"

190.en_source: "For the $450,000 we put into this beast it ought to be able to stand on its head, split the atom and fart The Star-Spangled Banner."
190.sl_trans: "Za 450.000 dolarjev, kolikor smo vložili v to zver, bi se morala postaviti na glavo, razdeliti atom in zapeti Zvezdnato zastavo."

191.sl_source: "Za 450000 $, ki smo jih vtaknili v to zver, bi morala stati na glavi, razcepiti atom in prdeti državno himno."

193.sl_trans: To je Terryjev odgovor na vse.

194.sl_source: To je Terryjeva rešitev za vse.
194.en_source: Kick it if it doesn't work.

195.sl_trans: Dvigni svojo rit nazaj na noge.

201.sl_source: "V redu je, šel bom okrog in tole zadevo spravil v pogon."
201.en_source: "It's okay, I can get around the other side and get this thing going."
201.sl_trans: "Nič hudega, lahko obidem drugo stran in začnem delati."

202.sl_source: "Ampak prisegel bi, da me stvar namenoma spravlja ob živce."
202.en_source: "But I tell you, I would swear this thing's purposefully trying to piss me off!"
202.sl_trans: "Ampak povem ti, prisegel bi, da me ta stvar namerno poskuša razjeziti!"

209.sl_source: "Manjši potresi, toda točno sredi njih sta."
209.en_source: "They're minor quakes, but they're right in the middle of it."
209.sl_trans: "Gre za manjše potrese, vendar so ravno v središču."

210.en_source: We should tell them to call it a day.
210.sl_trans: Morali bi jim reči, naj to končajo.

220.en_source: We can hear you, Go ahead.

222.en_source: "He's got a broken leg, by the looks of it here."

223.en_source: We need the chopper down here fast.

228.en_source: Send in the chopper right now.

229.sl_source: "Ne morem verjeti, da kamera po takem udarcu še dela."
229.en_source: I can't believe the camera's still working after taking a hit like that.
229.sl_trans: Ne morem verjeti, da fotoaparat še vedno deluje po takšnem udarcu.

233.en_source: "All right, hang on a second, okay?"

234.en_source: "Paul, the son-of-a-bitch pilot wants to renegotiate his rate."
234.sl_trans: "Paul, ta zlobni pilot se želi ponovno pogajati o svoji tarifi."

237.en_source: We're coming up to the rim of the crater.

238.en_source: Do you have a visual on us?

239.sl_source: "Točno pod vami sva, kakih 200 m pod južno steno."
239.en_source: "We're just below you, about 600 feet down off the south face."
239.sl_trans: "Smo tik pod vami, približno 600 metrov nižje od južne stene."

241.sl_source: "Še enkrat gremo okrog, vrgli vama bomo vrv in vaju potegnili gor."
241.en_source: We'll go around again and try to drop you a cable and then hoist you out of there.
241.sl_trans: Ponovno bomo šli naokrog in vas poskušali spustiti s kablom, nato pa vas dvigniti od tam.

257.sl_source: "Nočem težiti, ampak v mestu bi morali razglasiti preplah."
257.en_source: "I don't want to talk out of turn, but you should put this town on alert."
257.sl_trans: "Nočem govoriti na pamet, vendar bi morali to mesto opozoriti na nevarnost."

258.en_source: There's a lot of activity up there.

260.sl_source: Nočem sprožiti panike zaradi manjših tektonskih sunkov.
260.en_source: I don't want to cause a panic over minor tectonic quakes.
260.sl_trans: Ne želim povzročati panike zaradi manjših tektonskih potresov.

262.en_source: The biggest one we measured was a 2.9-
262.sl_trans: Največji, ki smo ga izmerili, je imel 2,9-

263.en_source: I don't give a damn if it was-
263.sl_trans: Vseeno mi je, ali je bil...

264.sl_source: Ti sunki so bili prekleto plitvi.

265.en_source: I was up there, I felt them.
265.sl_trans: Bil sem tam zgoraj, čutil sem jih.

268.en_source: This thing is going to blow.

270.sl_source: "Ne dovolim, da bi strašili ljudi zaradi ugibanj in slutenj!"
270.en_source: I'm not going to have my people scaring everyone because of guesswork and hunches!
270.sl_trans: Ne bom dovolil, da moji ljudje strašijo vse zaradi ugibanj in slutenj!

271.sl_source: "Čez 48 ur bo vse jasno, ti pa se zberi."
271.en_source: "Another 48 hours will tell the tale, and you get a grip."
271.sl_trans: "Še 48 ur bo pokazalo, kaj se bo zgodilo, in ti se boš oprijel."

274.sl_source: "Zdravnik pravi, da bom lahko šel, če je le z glavo vse v redu."
274.en_source: My doc says I can leave as soon as they make sure my head's okay.
274.sl_trans: Doktor pravi, da lahko odidem takoj, ko se prepričajo, da je z mojo glavo vse v redu.

275.sl_source: Potem se pa vidimo čez deset let.
275.sl_trans: "Dobro, potem se vidimo čez deset let."

276.sl_source: Pajek se ti je samo oddolžil za vse tvoje brce v rit.
276.en_source: Spider Legs was just getting even with you for all the kicks in the butt you gave him.
276.sl_trans: Pajkove noge so se ti želele maščevati za vse tvoje brce v rit.

278.sl_source: "Morate mi pomagati prepričati Paula, da ima gora resne namene."
278.en_source: I'll need your help to convince Paul that this mountain means business.
278.sl_trans: Potrebujem vašo pomoč, da prepričam Paula, da ta gora misli resno.

279.sl_source: "Nerad se strinjam s Paulom, toda ni pravih dokazov, da bi se dogajalo kaj čudnega."
279.en_source: I hate to agree with Paul but there's no real evidence that anything weird is going on.
279.sl_trans: Nerad se strinjam s Paulom, vendar ni pravih dokazov, da se dogaja kaj čudnega.

280.sl_source: Tako kot pri gori Baker v 70-ih.
280.en_source: Just like Mount Baker in the '70s.
280.sl_trans: Tako kot Mount Baker v 70. letih prejšnjega stoletja.

282.sl_source: "Srednješolski učitelj fizike mi je povedal, da žaba, če jo daš v vrelo vodo, skoči ven."
282.en_source: "My ninth-grade science teacher once told me that if you put a frog in boiling water, it'll jump right out."
282.sl_trans: "Moj učitelj naravoslovja v devetem razredu mi je nekoč rekel, da če damo žabo v vrelo vodo, bo takoj skočila ven."

283.sl_source: "Če pa jo daš v mrzlo vodo in jo počasi segrevaš, bo sedela v njej in se počasi skuhala."
283.en_source: But if you put it in cold water and heat it up gradually it'll just sit there and slowly boil to death.
283.sl_trans: Če pa ga postavite v hladno vodo in jo postopoma segrevate, bo le sedel in počasi vrel do smrti.

284.sl_source: "Harry, je to tvoj recept za žabjo juho?"
284.en_source: "What's that, Harry, your recipe for frog soup?"
284.sl_trans: "Kaj je to, Harry, tvoj recept za žabjo juho?"

286.sl_source: "Če bi danes prišli sem, bi vedeli, da smo v vroči vodi, in bi razglasili preplah."
286.en_source: "If we got here today, we'd know we were in hot water and we'd put this town on alert."
286.sl_trans: "Če bi prišli danes, bi vedeli, da smo se znašli v težavah, in to mesto bi bilo v pripravljenosti."

287.en_source: Take a look, The seismic activity is nil.
287.sl_trans: Oglejte si, Seizmična aktivnost je nična.

289.en_source: And take a look over here.

291.en_source: It's been like that all week.

294.sl_source: Naprave ne kažejo nobene spremembe v obliki gore.
294.en_source: The tiltmeters don't show any change in the mountain's shape.
294.sl_trans: Merilniki nagiba ne kažejo nobenih sprememb v obliki gore.

295.sl_source: "Videli smo vse, kar je ta gora nameravala storiti."
295.en_source: I think we've seen all this big baby's going to do.
295.sl_trans: Mislim, da smo videli vse, kar bo naredil ta veliki otrok.

296.sl_trans: Gora je povezana z električno napeljavo.

297.en_source: We got all our equipment in place.

298.sl_source: Odslej lahko opazujemo vse od doma.
298.en_source: We can keep an eye on things from home from now on.
298.sl_trans: Odslej lahko stvari spremljamo od doma.

300.sl_source: Videli smo že take premore v aktivnosti.
300.en_source: We've seen lulls like this in activity before.
300.sl_trans: Takšna zatišja v dejavnosti smo videli že prej.

301.sl_source: "Če smo pametni, bomo še par dni počakali."
301.en_source: "If we're wise, we'll give it a couple of days."
301.sl_trans: "Če smo pametni, bomo temu namenili nekaj dni."

302.sl_source: "Obljubil sem ti dva dni, dal sem ti en teden."
302.en_source: "I promised you two days, I gave it a week."
302.sl_trans: "Obljubil sem ti dva dni, pa sem ti dal teden dni."

303.en_source: "First thing in the morning, we are out of here."

304.sl_source: "Rachel, še vedno morava kdaj na večerjo."
304.en_source: "Rachel, we still have to have that dinner."

319.en_source: What do you do for fun?

323.sl_source: "Zabava je nekaj, kar doživljaš, ko nimaš otrok, gostilne in vodenja mesta."
323.en_source: "Fun is what you have when you don't have two children a business, and a town to run."
323.sl_trans: "Zabava je tisto, kar imaš, če nimaš dveh otrok, podjetja in mesta, ki ga moraš voditi."

326.sl_source: "Preden odidemo, sem se vam hotel zahvaliti za gostoljubje."
326.en_source: Before we took off I just wanted to say thanks for all the hospitality.
326.sl_trans: Preden smo odleteli, sem se želel zahvaliti za vso gostoljubnost.

328.sl_source: "Zelo lepo, da tako pravite, toda gotovo vam ni žal, da odhajamo."
328.en_source: "That's awfully nice of you to say that, but I'm sure you're not sorry to see us go."
328.sl_trans: "To je zelo lepo, da ste tako rekli, vendar sem prepričan, da vam ni žal, da gremo."

329.sl_source: "Naša navzočnost tu škodi poslu, kajne, Paul?"
329.en_source: "Our presence here is bad for business, right, Paul?"
329.sl_trans: "Naša navzočnost tukaj je slaba za posel, kajne, Paul?"

332.en_source: "Well, it's late and I have to let my babysitter get home."
332.sl_trans: "Pozno je in moram pustiti varuško, da pride domov."

339.sl_trans: Želim si, da ne bi odšel.

341.sl_source: "Najbrž res ni treba, da bi bili tu."
341.en_source: I guess we don't really have to be here.
341.sl_trans: Mislim, da nam v resnici ni treba biti tukaj.

342.en_source: We can watch this mountain from Portland.
342.sl_trans: To goro lahko opazujemo iz Portlanda.

343.sl_source: "Vseeno si želim, da ne bi odšli."
343.en_source: I still wish you weren't leaving.
343.sl_trans: Še vedno si želim, da ne bi odšla.

346.sl_source: Zdaj bo imela dva tedna o čem govoriti.
346.en_source: That'll give her something to talk about for a couple of weeks.
346.sl_trans: Tako bo imela nekaj tednov o čem govoriti.

362.en_source: "Well, maybe I should make some coffee."

363.en_source: "No, Rachel, I don't want any coffee.

365.sl_source: "Res mislim, da bi nama morala skuhati kavo."
365.en_source: I really think I should make us some coffee.
365.sl_trans: Mislim, da bi nama morala skuhati kavo.

366.sl_source: "Ne vem, kako naj ti to povem."
366.en_source: I don't know how to tell you this.
366.sl_trans: Ne vem, kako naj vam to povem.

367.sl_source: Nikoli mi ni bilo preveč mar za tvojo kavo.
367.en_source: I've never really cared for your coffee.
367.sl_trans: Nikoli mi ni bilo mar za vašo kavo.

368.sl_source: Zelo dolgo nisem bila z nikomer.
368.en_source: I haven't been with anybody in a long time.
368.sl_trans: Že dolgo nisem bila z nikomer.

370.en_source: But you know what they say.

371.sl_trans: To je kot vožnja s kolesom.

378.sl_source: "Mislim, da bo šla takoj nazaj spat."
378.en_source: I think she'll go right back to sleep.
378.sl_trans: Mislim, da bo takoj spet zaspala.

379.sl_source: "Prosim te, ljubi Bog, naj gre nazaj spat."
379.en_source: "Please, dear God in heaven, let her go back to sleep."
379.sl_trans: "Prosim, dragi Bog v nebesih, naj gre nazaj spat."

392.sl_source: "Enako stvar sem videl na Filipinih, preden je izbruhnila gora Pinatubo."
392.en_source: I saw the same thing in the Philippines on Mount Pinatubo before she blew.
392.sl_trans: Enako sem videl na Filipinih na gori Pinatubo, preden je eksplodirala.

395.en_source: I've got that scientific evidence you need.
395.sl_trans: Imam znanstvene dokaze, ki jih potrebujete.

397.sl_source: Pravkar sem bil v mestnem vodnem zbiralniku.
397.en_source: I've just come from the town's water supply.
397.sl_trans: Pravkar sem prišel iz mestnega vodovoda.

400.en_source: The quakes are beginning to swarm.

405.en_source: "Sir, is that the best you can do for us?"
405.sl_trans: "Gospod, ali je to vse, kar lahko storite za nas?"

407.sl_source: Narodna garda lahko pride šele jutri.
407.en_source: The National Guard can't be here until tomorrow.
407.sl_trans: Nacionalna garda ne more priti do jutri.

408.en_source: How much time do you think we've got?
408.sl_trans: Koliko časa misliš, da imamo na voljo?
